  "ideas": {
    "intro": "Ideas for projects, activities, books, games, and more for students with a high level of interest.",
    "terms": [
      {
        "term": 1,
        "title": "Term 1",
        "items": [
          {
            "id": "rec3MNY5FDpX72DUt",
            "term": 1,
            "sort": "",
            "content": "[ ] Take a look at the solar system with this [interactive map](https://www.solarsystemscope.com/).\n[ ] Check out these [skywatching tips](https://science.nasa.gov/skywatching/) from NASA and go skywatching on a clear night.\n[ ] Set up a simple weather station to watch through the year."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "term": 2,
        "title": "Term 2",
        "items": [
          {
            "id": "recrIvjTA7LdiYQ0j",
            "term": 2,
            "sort": "",
            "content": "[ ] Create a [simple closed terrarium](https://climatekids.nasa.gov/mini-garden/) to watch the water cycle continuously.\n[ ] You can also create a [water cycle in a bag](https://www.sciencemuseumok.org/smoathome/try-see-water-cycle-bag).\n[ ] Play a [guessing game](https://www.kids-pages.com/folders/worksheets/Nature/SeasonsGuess.pdf) giving hints one at a time about which season you are describing. Try to guess the answer with the least number of hints. Here are some sample clues."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "term": 3,
        "title": "Term 3",
        "items": [
          {
            "id": "recrKMRfYLaybhpeJ",
            "term": 3,
            "sort": "",
            "content": "[ ] This [National Geographic page](https://education.nationalgeographic.org/resource/maps-and-models/) has information on maps of familiar places along with simple questions to explore those maps.\n[ ] Print or copy a world map and take it with you to a zoo. Mark which continent each animal lives in on your map.\n[ ] Choose favorite picture books from your shelves or the library and find the character's home on a map. Suggestions include Paddington Bear, Anna Hibiscus, Madeline, etc."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
